deviations.msg: The correct UD label for abbreviations is 'Abbr=Yes'.
The correct UD label for foreign words is 'Foreign=Yes'.
The correct UD label for typos is 'Typo=Yes'.
The correct UD label for possessive pronouns is 'Poss=Yes'.
The correct UD label for reflexive pronouns is 'Reflex=Yes'.
Did you mean 'NounType=Clf'?
The correct UD label for interrogative pronouns is 'PronType=Int'.
The correct UD label for reflexive pronouns is 'PronType=Prs' together with 'Reflex=Yes'.
The correct UD feature for possessor's person is 'Person[psor]'.
The correct UD feature for possessor's number is 'Number[psor]'.
Did you mean 'Deixis=Prox|Med|Remt|...'?
Did you mean 'Deixis=Med'?
Did you mean 'NumForm=Word'?
The correct UD label for non-human animacy/gender is 'Nhum'.
The correct UD label for the special form of noun after numeral is 'Number=Count'.
The correct UD label for oblique case is 'Case=Acc'.
The correct UD label for comparative case is 'Case=Cmp'.
The correct UD label for temporal case is 'Case=Tem'.
The correct UD v2 label for prospective aspect is 'Aspect=Prosp'.
Use 'Aspect=Perf' to distinguish perfect from other forms.
The correct UD label for preterit is 'Tense=Past'.
The correct UD label for conditional mood is 'Mood=Cnd'.
The correct UD label for conjunctive/subjunctive mood is 'Mood=Sub'.
The correct UD label for conjunctive/subjunctive mood is 'Mood=Sub'.
The correct UD label for quotative mood is 'Mood=Qot'.
The correct UD label for antipassive voice is 'Voice=Antip'.
The correct UD label for finite verbs is 'VerbForm=Fin'.
The correct UD v2 label for transgressive/converb is 'VerbForm=Conv'.
If a feature does not apply to a word, UD simply omits the feature.
